{"id":36223,"title":"Percutaneous corrective osteotomy for Kirner's deformity: a case report.","abstract":"Kirner's deformity is a rare skeletal deformity first described in Germany in 1927. It is characterized by progressive palmar-radial curvature of the distal phalanx of the small finger. Here, we present the case of a 15-year-old boy with Kirner's deformity in both little fingers, who was treated with percutaneous corrective osteotomy. This was followed by a successful outcome after 36 months. ","date":"2014-04-04","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24590256","annotations":[{"name":"Germany","weight":0.602659,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germany"},{"name":"Distal phalanges","weight":0.530897,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Distal_phalanges"},{"name":"Finger","weight":0.492641,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finger"},{"name":"Phalanx bone","weight":0.25135,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phalanx_bone"},{"name":"Distal","weight":0.150778,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Distal"},{"name":"Skeleton","weight":0.137357,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skeleton"},{"name":"Osteotomy","weight":0.119639,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Osteotomy"},{"name":"Little finger","weight":0.10095,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Little_finger"},{"name":"Curvature","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Curvature"},{"name":"Deformity","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deformity"},{"name":"Percutaneous","weight":0.0152478,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Percutaneous"},{"name":"Case report","weight":0.0148276,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Case_report"},{"name":"Alpha taxonomy","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/